    "created_at": "2016-09-13T23:24:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-13T23:24:08Z",
    "body": "Personally I've always used the bounce workaround that you mentioned.  Sending a wrapped version of the message to the main process that then forwards it on the target renderer process.  But I've never needed the performance your use case appears to require.\n\nIt sounds you like might be better served hosting a localhost RPC server in one renderer process and communicating with that from the other?\n"
