    "created_at": "2016-09-14T06:27:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-14T06:27:41Z",
    "body": "@paulcbetts Yeah `sendTo` still goes to the main process and it has to, it is not possible to send messages between renderer processes directly because Chromium designed so for security.\n\nIf you really want to get away from the main process you have to write IPC code from scratch, with either's Node's `net` module or Chromium's `ipc` component.\n"
